cience is recognized as a provider of universal and democratic truth, because
 the system is independent from the role of observer.
 This paradigm is revisited in quantum mechanics because the knowledge of
 the system might be part of the system itself.
 This means that we need to write the apparatus, by which we get knowledge,
 into the global Hamiltonian.
 In jargon, the apparatus becomes 
